"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155404","Deputy Prime Minister","false","2014-11-20","<p>The Government is keeping the current 15 year time limit for all UK citizens living overseas under consideration. There are no plans to change the law at the present time.</p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","214117","2014-11-20T17:50:54.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155404/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155404/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155404/answer",,,,,,,,,,"58","Deputy Prime Minister","Deputy Prime Minister","2014-11-11","Voting Rights: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Deputy Prime Minister, if he will extend the overseas voting rights to UK citizens living in EU countries to 25 years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Baroness McIntosh of Pickering","Thirsk and Malton","Miss Anne McIntosh","214234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155405","Cabinet Office","false","2014-11-19","<p>Information on Ministerial Travel is published at:</p><p>(i) <a title="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200708/cmhansrd/cm080722/wmstext/80722m0008.htm" href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200708/cmhansrd/cm080722/wmstext/80722m0008.htm" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200708/cmhansrd/cm080722/wmstext/80722m0008.htm</a></p><p>(ii) <a title="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/cm090716/wmstext/90716m0009.htm" href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/cm090716/wmstext/90716m0009.htm" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/cm090716/wmstext/90716m0009.htm</a></p><p>(iii) <a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201011/cmhansrd/cm101028/wmstext/101028m0001.htm#10102827000372" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201011/cmhansrd/cm101028/wmstext/101028m0001.htm#10102827000372</a></p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-11-19T17:02:59.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155405/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155405/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155405/answer",,,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-11-11","Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what total amount his Department spent on ministerial travel by (a) the Government Car and Despatch Agency and (b) other car hire in (i) 2007-08, (ii) 2008-09 and (iii) 2009-10.","false","Biography information for John Glen","Salisbury","John Glen","214269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155406","Cabinet Office","false","2014-11-17","<p>MyCSP was spun-out as a mutual joint venture in May 2012. Mutualising MyCSP was good for staff, taxpayers and for the service they provide to pensioners. MyCSP will almost halve the cost of administering pensions within a decade, while improving services which were variable before. Employees of MyCSP have benefited through dividends, which they have received in both years since mutualisation. Staff survey figures show rising staff engagement and a decline in sickness absence.</p><p>Legacy problems were inherited from the previous administrator. MyCSP experienced exceptionally high volumes of calls following the transfer of pensioner payroll administration to MyCSP from the previous supplier. Call volumes have now declined substantially and MyCSP have switched all available resources to dealing with outstanding cases.</p><p>The overwhelming majority of 658,000 existing pensioners were paid accurately and MyCSP is working to reduce delays and clear any remaining backlog of work as quickly as possible.</p><p>MyCSP processes all pension awards by the due date where it holds all the necessary information from the employer and member needed to calculate the award.</p><p>Between 01 October 2013 and 30 September 2014 MyCSP processed 17,380 retirement awards. Of those, 16,865 (97%) were processed on time. In some cases, delays resulted from incorrect information being provided to MyCSP.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","214396 ; 214397","2014-11-17T17:21:42.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155406/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155406/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155406/answer",,,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-11-11","Civil Servants: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the reason is for the time taken by MyCSP to answer telephone calls from customers.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","214399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155407","Cabinet Office","false","2014-11-19","<p>The Cabinet Office administers the Public Duty Cost Allowance. Claims are processed by the Cabinet Office’s finance function, and all claims are subject to audit as part of the annual audit of Cabinet Office expenditure, by both internal audit and the National Audit Office. Relevant supporting documentation and corroboration are made available to the Cabinet Office finance team who administer the payments.</p><p>The current limit for the PDCA is £115,000. The limit is reviewed on an annual basis.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","214391","2014-11-19T17:03:22.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155407/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155407/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155407/answer",,,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-11-11","Public Duty Costs Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which office administers the public duty costs allowance for former Prime Ministers; and what checks are made to ensure that claims against that allowance meet its criteria.","false","Biography information for Pete Wishart","Perth and North Perthshire","Pete Wishart","214390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155408","Cabinet Office","false","2014-11-17","<p>MyCSP was spun-out as a mutual joint venture in May 2012. Mutualising MyCSP was good for staff, taxpayers and for the service they provide to pensioners. MyCSP will almost halve the cost of administering pensions within a decade, while improving services which were variable before. Employees of MyCSP have benefited through dividends, which they have received in both years since mutualisation. Staff survey figures show rising staff engagement and a decline in sickness absence.</p><p>Legacy problems were inherited from the previous administrator. MyCSP experienced exceptionally high volumes of calls following the transfer of pensioner payroll administration to MyCSP from the previous supplier. Call volumes have now declined substantially and MyCSP have switched all available resources to dealing with outstanding cases.</p><p>The overwhelming majority of 658,000 existing pensioners were paid accurately and MyCSP is working to reduce delays and clear any remaining backlog of work as quickly as possible.</p><p>MyCSP processes all pension awards by the due date where it holds all the necessary information from the employer and member needed to calculate the award.</p><p>Between 01 October 2013 and 30 September 2014 MyCSP processed 17,380 retirement awards. Of those, 16,865 (97%) were processed on time. In some cases, delays resulted from incorrect information being provided to MyCSP.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","214397 ; 214399","2014-11-17T17:21:42.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155408/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155408/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155408/answer",,,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-11-11","Civil Servants: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many civil servants who have retired in the last 12 months and applied for their pension have experienced delays in receiving payments.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","214396"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155409","Cabinet Office","false","2014-11-17","<p>MyCSP was spun-out as a mutual joint venture in May 2012. Mutualising MyCSP was good for staff, taxpayers and for the service they provide to pensioners. MyCSP will almost halve the cost of administering pensions within a decade, while improving services which were variable before. Employees of MyCSP have benefited through dividends, which they have received in both years since mutualisation. Staff survey figures show rising staff engagement and a decline in sickness absence.</p><p>Legacy problems were inherited from the previous administrator. MyCSP experienced exceptionally high volumes of calls following the transfer of pensioner payroll administration to MyCSP from the previous supplier. Call volumes have now declined substantially and MyCSP have switched all available resources to dealing with outstanding cases.</p><p>The overwhelming majority of 658,000 existing pensioners were paid accurately and MyCSP is working to reduce delays and clear any remaining backlog of work as quickly as possible.</p><p>MyCSP processes all pension awards by the due date where it holds all the necessary information from the employer and member needed to calculate the award.</p><p>Between 01 October 2013 and 30 September 2014 MyCSP processed 17,380 retirement awards. Of those, 16,865 (97%) were processed on time. In some cases, delays resulted from incorrect information being provided to MyCSP.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","214396 ; 214399","2014-11-17T17:21:42.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155409/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155409/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155409/answer",,,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-11-11","Civil Servants: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the average time taken is to make a first pension payment to a recently retired civil servant.","false","Biography information for Derek Twigg","Halton","Derek Twigg","214397"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155410","Cabinet Office","false","2014-11-19","<p>The Cabinet Office administers the Public Duty Cost Allowance. Claims are processed by the Cabinet Office’s finance function, and all claims are subject to audit as part of the annual audit of Cabinet Office expenditure, by both internal audit and the National Audit Office. Relevant supporting documentation and corroboration are made available to the Cabinet Office finance team who administer the payments.</p><p>The current limit for the PDCA is £115,000. The limit is reviewed on an annual basis.</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","214390","2014-11-19T17:03:22.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155410/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155410/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155410/answer",,,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-11-11","Public Duty Costs Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the limit is of the public duty costs allowance for former Prime Ministers; and when that limit will next be reviewed.","false","Biography information for Pete Wishart","Perth and North Perthshire","Pete Wishart","214391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155411","Cabinet Office","false","2014-11-17","<p>My Department aims to respond to all correspondence within 15 working days. Business processes are regularly reviewed to ensure we meet this target.</p><p>Guidance on handling correspondence from Members of Parliament, Peers, MEPs and Members of devolved Administrations will be updated in due course.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/61196/guide-handling-gov-correspondence.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/61196/guide-handling-gov-correspondence.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude",,"2014-11-17T16:40:46.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155411/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155411/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155411/answer",,,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-11-11","Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how often his Department reviews its processes regarding the logging of emails, letters and other correspondence received; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","214245"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155412","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-21","<p>(a) This information has already been published and can be found at:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><ol><li><p><a title="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200708/cmhansrd/cm080722/wmstext/80722m0008.htm" href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200708/cmhansrd/cm080722/wmstext/80722m0008.htm" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200708/cmhansrd/cm080722/wmstext/80722m0008.htm</a></p></li><li><p><a title="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/cm090716/wmstext/90716m0009.htm" href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/cm090716/wmstext/90716m0009.htm" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/cm090716/wmstext/90716m0009.htm</a></p></li><li><p><a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201011/cmhansrd/cm101028/wmstext/101028m0001.htm#10102827000372" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201011/cmhansrd/cm101028/wmstext/101028m0001.htm#10102827000372</a></p></li></ol><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>(b) Expenditure on other car hire could not be extracted without exceeding the statutory disproportionate costs threshold.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-11-21T12:56:20.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155412/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155412/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155412/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-11","Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what total amount his Department spent on ministerial travel by (a) the Government Car and Despatch Agency and (b) other car hire in (i) 2007-08, (ii) 2008-09 and (iii) 2009-10.","false","Biography information for John Glen","Salisbury","John Glen","214284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155413","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-17","<p>The Multilateral Competent Authority Agreement (MCAA) signed in Berlin is the instrument which will give effect to exchange under the new global standard of automatic tax information exchange by its signatories. At the signing event in Berlin 51 countries and jurisdictions signed the MCAA and we expect the other countries committed to implementation to do so shortly.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Implementation of the global standard will lead to step change in the international communities’ ability to tackle offshore tax evasion.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2014-11-17T16:47:53.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155413/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155413/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155413/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-11","Taxation: Treaties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the scope of the Multilateral Competent Authority Agreement on automatic exchange of taxpayer information recently signed in Berlin; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mark Durkan","Foyle","Mark Durkan","214326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155414","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-20","<p>HM Treasury continually reviews its processes for logging emails, letters and other correspondence received.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We take correspondence very seriously and aim to respond to all correspondence requiring a reply within 15 working days of receipt.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Guidance on handling correspondence from Members of Parliament, Peers, MEPs and Members of devolved Administrations is available online at the following link - https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/61196/guide-handling-gov-correspondence.pdf</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-11-20T13:52:16.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155414/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155414/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155414/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-11","Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how often his Department reviews its processes regarding the logging of emails, letters and other correspondence received; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","214258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155415","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-24","<p>As made clear during our G8 Presidency, we are committed to helping developing countries benefit from increased tax transparency including the new global standard of automatic exchange of information. Since G20 Finance Ministers welcomed the Global Forum’s Roadmap in September, my officials and their counterparts in DfID and HMRC have engaged in discussions with a number of developing countries on the possibility of piloting implementation of the new global standard. These discussions are ongoing.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","214410","2014-11-24T13:53:20.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155415/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155415/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155415/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-11","Taxation: Developing Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how he plans to respond to the OECD's proposals on involvement of low income countries in development of the automatic exchange of tax payer information.","false","Biography information for Mark Durkan","Foyle","Mark Durkan","214411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155416","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-24","<p>The UK is at the forefront of multilateral action through the G20 and OECD to tackle the issue of tax avoidance by multinational enterprise. The UK used its Presidency of the G8 to successfully build international support for this work.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Work is well underway at the OECD, in the form of the Base Erosion and Profit Shifting (BEPS) project. The first phase of the BEPS project is now complete, with participants reaching agreement on seven reports which have been produced by the OECD and endorsed by G20 Finance Ministers at their Summit in Cairns 20-21 September.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Of these outputs, this government has already taken domestic action towards implementation. In September 2014 the UK announced it would be the first of 44 countries to formally commit to implementing the newly agreed BEPS output of a country-by-country reporting template.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Subsequently, in October 2014 the UK announced its commitment to publish a consultation on the BEPs project’s 2014 output to neutralise hybrid mismatches - a tax avoidance technique used by multinationals to exploit differences between countries’ tax rules to avoid paying tax in either country, or to obtain more tax relief against profits than they are entitled to.</p><p> </p><p>The BEPS project is due to finish by December 2015. In order to achieve success by creating effective recommendations for the remaining Actions, in line with the Action Plan, the collaboration and momentum of the process must continue.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As set out in the publication at Budget 14, one of the key principles underpinning the UK’s approach to the BEPS project is that the solutions should be consistent with the Government’s wish to promote UK growth and competitiveness.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Whilst the project will not be completed until the end of 2015, if we can achieve our goals, we will succeed in fundamentally changing the international tax landscape, and shift the balance of the rules in favour of tax authorities, enabling us to clamp down on those who refuse to play by the rules.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-11-24T16:54:10.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155416/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155416/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155416/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-11","Tax Avoidance: Multinational Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what his policy is on the Base Erosion and Profit Sharing process; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mark Durkan","Foyle","Mark Durkan","214412"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155417","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-20","<p>The St Petersburg Declaration refers to Action 11 of the G20-OECD Base Erosion and Profit Shifting project, which is developing an economic analysis to determine the scale and impact of aggressive tax planning by multinationals, including on the spillover effects into other countries. The UK supports this work.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-11-20T17:23:11.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155417/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155417/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155417/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-11","Taxation: Developing Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the G20's 2013 St Petersburg Declaration, what plans he has for a spillover analysis of the effects of UK tax rules on developing countries.","false","Biography information for Mark Durkan","Foyle","Mark Durkan","214389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155418","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-24","<p>As made clear during our G8 Presidency, we are committed to helping developing countries benefit from increased tax transparency including the new global standard of automatic exchange of information. Since G20 Finance Ministers welcomed the Global Forum’s Roadmap in September, my officials and their counterparts in DfID and HMRC have engaged in discussions with a number of developing countries on the possibility of piloting implementation of the new global standard. These discussions are ongoing.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","214411","2014-11-24T13:53:20.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155418/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155418/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155418/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-11","Taxation: Developing Countries","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will pilot a scheme on automatic information exchange with a developing country.","false","Biography information for Mark Durkan","Foyle","Mark Durkan","214410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155420","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-21","<p>The impact of the reclassification on the government’s financial position is set out in the OBR’s Economic and Fiscal Outlook as at March 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-11-21T12:58:26.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155420/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155420/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155420/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-11","Network Rail","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what impact the reclassification of Network Rail as a government body has had on (a) the financial position of the Government and (b) the financial position of Network Rail; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Tom Harris","Glasgow South","Mr Tom Harris","214213"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155421","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-20","<p>Public Sector Net Debt (PSND) is not currently geographically split and so only overall Public Sector Net Debt (PSND) has increased.</p><p> </p>","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Danny Alexander",,"2014-11-20T17:01:13.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155421/answer","Biography information for Danny Alexander","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155421/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155421/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-11","Network Rail","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether any proportion of Network Rail's debt has been allocated to the Scottish Government as a result of the reclassification of Network Rail as a government body on 1 September 2014.","false","Biography information for Mr Tom Harris","Glasgow South","Mr Tom Harris","214214"
