"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155548","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-01-12","<p>The Ministry of Justice has not issued guidance to court users on the use of the term ‘victim’.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-01-12T13:19:54.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155548/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155548/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155548/answer",,,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-11-11","Crime: Victims","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what guidance his Department gives court users on the use of the term victim at the pre-conviction stage of a court case.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","214195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155549","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-02-10","<p /> <p>(a) This information has already been published and can be found at:</p><p> </p><p>(i) <a title="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200708/cmhansrd/cm080722/wmstext/80722m0008.htm" href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200708/cmhansrd/cm080722/wmstext/80722m0008.htm" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200708/cmhansrd/cm080722/wmstext/80722m0008.htm</a></p><p>(ii) <a title="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/cm090716/wmstext/90716m0009.htm" href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/cm090716/wmstext/90716m0009.htm" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/cm090716/wmstext/90716m0009.htm</a></p><p>(iii) <a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201011/cmhansrd/cm101028/wmstext/101028m0001.htm#10102827000372" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201011/cmhansrd/cm101028/wmstext/101028m0001.htm#10102827000372</a></p><p> </p><p>(b) To provide the ministerial spend for the other car hire will incur disproportionate costs.</p><p> </p><p>Under this Government the number of ministerial cars in the Department has fallen from four to one and the cost to the taxpayer reduced by 91%.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-02-10T13:02:33.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155549/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155549/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155549/answer",,,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-11-11","Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what total amount his Department spent on ministerial travel by (a) the Government Car and Despatch Agency and (b) other car hire in (i) 2007-08, (ii) 2008-09 and (iii) 2009-10.","false","Biography information for John Glen","Salisbury","John Glen","214279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155550","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-12-08","<p /> <p>The Ministry of Justice uses an in-house data-handling system to log correspondence and assign it to the appropriate team for a response. The team that coordinates responses to the majority of correspondence gather briefly each day to manage their workload. This can involve suggestions from team members for improving processes, including logging. They meet more formally once a month, when improvements can also be proposed. The team meets once a fortnight with Ministers' private offices to review how correspondence is handled and issues monthly management information to members of the senior civil service responsible for correspondence handling in their teams, to focus on performance.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has a 15 working-day target to respond to Members. Guidance on handling correspondence from Members of Parliament, Peers, MEPs and Members of devolved Administrations is available online at the following link - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/61196/guide-handling-gov-correspondence.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/61196/guide-handling-gov-correspondence.pdf</a></p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-12-08T17:48:08.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155550/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155550/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155550/answer",,,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-11-11","Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how often his Department reviews its processes regarding the logging of emails, letters and other correspondence received; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","214254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155551","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-11-17","<p /> <p>In ‘Our Commitment to Victims’ the Government set out its plan for strengthening the protection for vulnerable victims by improving their experience at court. By March 2015 we will:</p><p>· devise a requirement that to be instructed in cases involving serious sexual offences, publicly-funded advocates must have undertaken approved specialist training on working with vulnerable victims and witnesses;</p><p>· give vulnerable witnesses greater opportunity to give evidence from a location away from court that better supports them to give their evidence, with at least one such location available in each court region;</p><p>· set out a programme for national roll-out of pre-trial cross-examination for child victims, subject to the evaluation of the pilots; and</p><p>· support the Director of Public Prosecutions’ consultation on providing better information and support to victims both before and at court so that they are better prepared for trials.</p><p> </p><p>And as we modernise the courts, we will ensure that victims’ needs are at the forefront of our plans.</p><p> </p><p>Taken together, these reforms will ensure that where victims give evidence, they can do so with in a less aggressive courtroom atmosphere, to reduce their anxiety.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-11-17T17:20:32.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155551/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155551/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155551/answer",,,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-11-11","Victim Support Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Written Statement of 13 October 2014, Official Report, column 13WS, on Our Commitment to Victims, what steps he is taking to improve the experience of going to court for vulnerable victims.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","214334"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155552","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-11-17","<p>We will enshrine the rights of victims in law by putting the key entitlements of the Victims’ Code into primary legislation. This will put the highest emphasis on the needs of victims. We expect this new victims’ law to be introduced in the next Parliament.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-11-17T16:55:07.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155552/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155552/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155552/answer",,,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-11-11","Victim Support Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Written Statement of 13 October 2014, Official Report, column 13WS, on Our Commitment to Victims, when he plans to publish legislative proposals on guaranteeing victims' rights.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","214333"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155553","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-11-17","<p /> <p>The Victims’ Information Service, which will be launched by March 2015, will consist of a national information line and a website for victims to find information about the criminal justice system and support services, in one place, for the first time. It will also signpost victims to local and national support services and to the relevant criminal justice agency if they want to know about their case or make a complaint.</p><p> </p><p>By April 2016, the Victims’ Information Service will provide more support for victims by enabling them to submit complaints to the relevant agency; provide feedback about their experiences; and ensure that those who most need it receive more tailored personal assistance to guide them through the system. We will continue to develop the service, post 2016, based on user feedback, to make further improvements and ensure that it continues to meet the needs of victims.</p><p> </p><p>We are currently scoping the detail of what the Victims’ Information Service will offer in accordance with user need and the projected costs will be informed by this process and will ensure the solution developed offers value for money. We are making more money than ever before available for services to support victims of crime, with a potential total budget of up to £100m per year. The costs of the Victims’ Information Service will be met from this budget.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","214336","2014-11-17T16:19:59.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155553/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155553/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155553/answer",,,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-11-11","Victim Support Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Written Statement of 13 October 2014, Official Report, column 13WS, on Our Commitment to Victims, what estimate he has made of expenditure on the proposed Victims' Information Service in each of the next three years; and from which budget that expenditure is drawn.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","214335"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155554","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-11-17","<p>The Victims’ Information Service, which will be launched by March 2015, will consist of a national information line and a website for victims to find information about the criminal justice system and support services, in one place, for the first time. It will also signpost victims to local and national support services and to the relevant criminal justice agency if they want to know about their case or make a complaint.</p><p> </p><p>By April 2016, the Victims’ Information Service will provide more support for victims by enabling them to submit complaints to the relevant agency; provide feedback about their experiences; and ensure that those who most need it receive more tailored personal assistance to guide them through the system. We will continue to develop the service, post 2016, based on user feedback, to make further improvements and ensure that it continues to meet the needs of victims.</p><p> </p><p>We are currently scoping the detail of what the Victims’ Information Service will offer in accordance with user need and the projected costs will be informed by this process and will ensure the solution developed offers value for money. We are making more money than ever before available for services to support victims of crime, with a potential total budget of up to £100m per year. The costs of the Victims’ Information Service will be met from this budget.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","214335","2014-11-17T16:19:59.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155554/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155554/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155554/answer",,,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-11-11","Victim Support Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to the Written Statement of 13 October 2014, Official Report, column 13WS, on Our Commitment to Victims, which services the proposed Victims' Information Service will provide.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","214336"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155555","Leader of the House","false","2014-11-19","<p>The information on ministerial travel is published at:</p><p>(i) <a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200708/cmhansrd/cm080722/wmstext/80722m0008.htm" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200708/cmhansrd/cm080722/wmstext/80722m0008.htm</a></p><p>(ii) <a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/cm090716/wmstext/90716m0009.htm" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200809/cmhansrd/cm090716/wmstext/90716m0009.htm</a></p><p>(iii) <a href="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201011/cmhansrd/cm101028/wmstext/101028m0001.htm#10102827000372" target="_blank">http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201011/cmhansrd/cm101028/wmstext/101028m0001.htm#10102827000372</a></p><p>The information requested for other car hire is not held centrally.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Mr William Hague",,"2014-11-19T12:03:39.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155555/answer","Biography information for Lord Hague of Richmond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155555/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155555/answer",,,,,,,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2014-11-11","Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, what total amount his Office spent on ministerial travel by (a) the Government Car and Despatch Agency and (b) other car hire in (i) 2007-08, (ii) 2008-09 and (iii) 2009-10.","false","Biography information for John Glen","Salisbury","John Glen","214280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155556","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-11-17","<p>Because of the devolution of policing and justice functions on 12 April 2010, and subsequent reconfiguration of the Northern Ireland Office, my Department does not hold figures for the periods prior to 2010; attempting to obtain this information would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-11-17T13:56:45.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155556/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155556/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155556/answer",,,,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-11-11","Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what total amount her Office spent on ministerial travel by (a) the Government Car and Despatch Agency and (b) other car hire in (i) 2007-08, (ii) 2008-09 and (iii) 2009-10.","false","Biography information for John Glen","Salisbury","John Glen","214281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155557","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-11-18","<p>The Department routinely reviews the process for logging correspondence in order to respond within our 21 working day target.</p><p>Guidance on handling correspondence from Members of Parliament, Peers, MEPs and Members of devolved Administrations is available online at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/61196/guide-handling-gov-correspondence.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/61196/guide-handling-gov-correspondence.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-11-18T13:55:08.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155557/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155557/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155557/answer",,,,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-11-11","Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how often her Department reviews its processes regarding the logging of emails, letters and other correspondence received; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","214255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155558","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-11-17","<p>No buildings owned by my Department have been sold in any of the years 2010, 2011, 2012, 2013 and 2014. My department has responsibility for Hillsborough Castle and rents accommodation at both Stormont House in Belfast and 1 Horse Guards Road, London.</p><p>In 2013, the Northern Ireland Office moved its London office from Millbank to 1 Horse Guards, saving in the region of £1m per year. In 2014, management of Hillsborough Castle was transferred to Historic Royal Palaces which will also deliver substantial annual savings for the taxpayer.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-11-17T13:58:25.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155558/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155558/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155558/answer",,,,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-11-11","Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many buildings her Department sold in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013 and (e) 2014.","false","Biography information for Valerie  Vaz","Walsall South","Valerie Vaz","214222"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155560","Prime Minister","false","2014-11-17","<p>None.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2014-11-17T17:54:37.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155560/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155560/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155560/answer",,,,,,,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2014-11-11","Ofcom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, whether he has made representations to Ofcom in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","214229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155561","Prime Minister","false","2014-11-17","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2014-11-17T17:55:13.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155561/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155561/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155561/answer",,,,,,,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2014-11-11","Official Hospitality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, at which events he has been officially represented at by someone who is not a member of the Government since 2010.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","214328"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155562","Scotland Office","false","2014-11-18","<p>The Scotland Office keeps its logging processes under periodic review and aims to respond to all correspondence within 15 working days.</p><p>Guidance on handling correspondence from Members of Parliament, Peers, MEPs and Members of devolved Administrations is available online at the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/61196/guide-handling-gov-correspondence.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/61196/guide-handling-gov-correspondence.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-11-18T15:07:03.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155562/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155562/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155562/answer",,,,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-11-11","Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how often his Department reviews its processes regarding the logging of emails, letters and other correspondence received; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Simon Kirby","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","214256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155563","Scotland Office","false","2014-11-18","<p>The Scotland Office spend on ministerial travel by the Government Car and Despatch Agency and other car hire in 2007-08, 2008-09 and 2009-10 was as follows:</p><p><strong>2007-08</strong> £ 57,913.40</p><p><strong>2008-09</strong> £ 98,602.88</p><p><strong>2009-10</strong> £145,508.75</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-11-18T14:56:23.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155563/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155563/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155563/answer",,,,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-11-11","Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what total amount his Department spent on ministerial travel by (a) the Government Car and Despatch Agency and (b) other car hire in (i) 2007-08, (ii) 2008-09 and (iii) 2009-10.","false","Biography information for John Glen","Salisbury","John Glen","214282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155564","Scotland Office","false","2014-11-18","<p>The Scotland Office does not employ staff directly. All staff that join the Office do so on an assignment, secondment or loan agreement from other Government bodies. All staff on such arrangements are paid more than the rate defined by the Living Wage Foundation.</p><p>The Scotland Office has one contract which provides security for the office in Edinburgh. The Scotland Office does not set the wages paid by the contractors to its workers; however, the wage paid by the contractor is above the national minimum wage. Otherwise, the Office uses framework contracts for building services held by the Ministry of Justice and the Scottish Government.</p><p> </p>","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael",,"2014-11-18T14:38:26.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155564/answer","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155564/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155564/answer",,,,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-11-11","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, whether (a) all staff in his Department's offices in London and Edinburgh and (b) contractors who provide services in his Departments properties are paid the living wage as defined by the Living Wage Foundation.","false","Biography information for Margaret Curran","Glasgow East","Margaret Curran","214406"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155566","Scotland Office","false","2014-11-18","<p>The Scotland Office has not owned any buildings since its inception in 1999 and did not sell any buildings in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013 and (e) 2014.</p><p>The Scotland Office is making an appropriate contribution to the Government’s land and property strategy by making more efficient use of its leasehold property and making more space available to other government bodies in its buildings.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-11-18T14:58:06.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155566/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155566/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155566/answer",,,,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-11-11","Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many buildings his Department sold in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013 and (e) 2014.","false","Biography information for Valerie  Vaz","Walsall South","Valerie Vaz","214223"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155567","Department for Transport","false","2014-11-17","<p>The requested information is not available in the format requested and can only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Transport reviews assets and land and property holdings on an ongoing basis and recently completed the Strategic Land &amp; Property Review to identify capital receipts in SR15. As and when appropriate any land or property holdings deemed surplus are promptly identified and disposed of in accordance with business needs.</p><p> </p><p>This has resulted in reductions in the cost of the department estate and improved space efficiency as reported in the annual State of the Estate Report:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>2010-11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total cost of the estate</strong></p></td><td><p>£166,096,850</p></td><td><p>£161,858,767</p></td><td><p>£154,653,361</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Occupied space (m2) per FTE</strong></p></td><td><p>12.4</p></td><td><p>11.9</p></td><td><p>10.3</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>In addition the Department for Transport has contributed land capable of delivering 3,752 homes to the Public Sector Land Programme during the current parliament, we are continuing to rationalise our estate, delivering cost savings and better value for money for the taxpayer.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2014-11-17T10:59:17.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155567/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155567/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/155567/answer",,,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-11-11","Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many buildings his Department sold in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013 and (e) 2014.","false","Biography information for Valerie  Vaz","Walsall South","Valerie Vaz","214224"
