"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147432","Cabinet Office","false","2014-11-17","<p>A copy of the report was placed in the Library of the House on 6 November 2014.</p><p> </p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2014-11-17T16:37:55.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147432/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147432/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147432/answer",,,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-11-10","Community Development","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 6 November 2014 to Question 213129, when he plans to place the interim report in the Library.","false","Biography information for Lisa Nandy","Wigan","Lisa Nandy","214057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147433","Cabinet Office","false","2014-11-19","<p>The Prime Minister’s Office is an integral part of the Cabinet Office.</p><p>Since January 2011, as part of the Government’s transparency programme, details of procurement opportunities, tender documents and contracts worth over £10,000 are published online on Contracts Finder (<a href="https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder</a>), and the Crown Commercial Service (CCS) also publishes details of its contracts on its web site (<a href="http://ccs.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/" target="_blank">http://ccs.cabinetoffice.gov.uk/</a>).</p><p> </p>","Horsham","Mr Francis Maude","214014","2014-11-19T17:02:31.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147433/answer","Biography information for Lord Maude of Horsham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147433/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147433/answer",,,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-11-10","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many contracts signed by his Department with suppliers of services or consultants include a clause providing that if the contract is abrogated by the Government, the provider or consultant will be compensated for lost income since 2010.","false","Biography information for Austin Mitchell","Great Grimsby","Austin Mitchell","214001"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147434","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-17","<p>A publication on take-up of the Employment Allowance was published on Friday 7<sup>th</sup> November and is available on the GOV.UK website at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/employment-allowance-take-up-2014-to-2015-mid-year-estimate" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/employment-allowance-take-up-2014-to-2015-mid-year-estimate</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This contains mid-year estimates for 2014-15 of the number of employers benefitting from the Employment Allowance including breakdowns by region, sector, constituency and employer size.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>These statistics show that take-up has been very positive with 68% of all eligible business and charities across the UK having claimed the allowance so far.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","213965","2014-11-17T16:12:34.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147434/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147434/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147434/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-10","National Insurance Contributions: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many businesses in (a) Wales, (b) North Wales and (c) Aberconwy constituency are exempted from paying employer national insurance contributions.","false","Biography information for Guto Bebb","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","213964"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147435","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-20","<p>Since January 2011, central Government Departments have been required to publish on Contracts Finder information on the tenders issued and contracts they award with a value over £10,000</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/contracts-finder" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/contracts-finder</a></p><p> </p><p>In addition, Departments including HM Treasury routinely publish details of transactions over £25,000.</p><p> </p><p>Information relating to <em>the number of contracts that include </em><em>a clause providing that if the contract is abrogated by the Government, the provider or consultant will be compensated for lost income</em>, is not held centrally.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-11-20T13:49:17.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147435/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147435/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-10","Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many contracts signed by his Department with suppliers of services or consultants include a clause providing that if the contract is abrogated by the Government, the provider or consultant will be compensated for lost income since 2010.","false","Biography information for Austin Mitchell","Great Grimsby","Austin Mitchell","214017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147436","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-17","<p>A publication on take-up of the Employment Allowance was published on Friday 7<sup>th</sup> November and is available on the GOV.UK website at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/employment-allowance-take-up-2014-to-2015-mid-year-estimate" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/employment-allowance-take-up-2014-to-2015-mid-year-estimate</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This contains mid-year estimates for 2014-15 of the number of employers benefitting from the Employment Allowance including breakdowns by region, sector, constituency and employer size.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>These statistics show that take-up has been very positive with 68% of all eligible business and charities across the UK having claimed the allowance so far.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","213964","2014-11-17T16:12:34.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147436/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147436/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147436/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-10","Employment and Support Allowance: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate his Department has made of the number of employers in (a) Wales, (b) North Wales and (c) Aberconwy constituency who have not yet claimed employment and support allowance.","false","Biography information for Guto Bebb","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","213965"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147437","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-20","<p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs (HMRC) do not hold the information requested.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-11-20T17:13:18.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147437/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147437/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147437/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-10","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much has been recovered from people who fraudulently claimed tax credits in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","214040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147438","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-20","<p>The table below shows the central estimate of the levels of error and fraud in the tax credit system for each of the last five tax years.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td> </td><td><p><strong>2008-09</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2009-10</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010-11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p> </p><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Central estimate of Error and Fraud as a percentage of finalised tax credits entitlement</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>8.9%</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>7.8%</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>8.1%</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>7.3%</strong></p></td><td><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>7.0%</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Central estimate of the total net Error &amp; Fraud value (billion)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£2,110</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£2,060</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£2,270</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£2,090</strong></p></td><td><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong>£2,010</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The latest published statistics relating to tax credit error and fraud can be found in the attached link:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/316032/Random_Enquiry_2012-13_final.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/316032/Random_Enquiry_2012-13_final.pdf</a></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-11-20T17:05:15.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147438/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147438/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-10","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the value of tax credits which were claimed fraudulently in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","214041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147439","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-20","<p>GOV.UK provides the public with comprehensive <a href="https://www.gov.uk/browse/benefits/tax-credits" target="_blank">guidance</a> about tax credits, including a tax credits <a href="https://www.gov.uk/tax-credits-calculator" target="_blank">calculator</a> that people can use to assess their own eligibility. Our tax credits helpline advisers also provide advice and guidance to people who call to enquire about their eligibility.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC also works closely with voluntary and community sector organisations to ensure they have the right information available to help their customers understand potential eligibility for tax credits, and how to apply.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In addition to the channels above, HMRC runs an annual advertising campaign to promote the need for tax credits customers to renew their claims. The campaign uses a range of channels including national television, radio and digital marketing, and reaches a wide audience across the UK.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-11-20T17:12:26.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147439/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147439/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147439/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-10","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps his Department (a) has taken and (b) is taking to make people who are eligible for tax credits aware of the opportunity to claim.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","214042"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147440","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-20","<p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs (HMRC) do not hold the information requested.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-11-20T17:19:14.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147440/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147440/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-10","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the value of tax credits which were not claimed in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","214043"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147441","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-20","<p>Resource is flexibly deployed between benefits and credits to meet customer demand. A specific figure for tax credits cannot be provided.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-11-20T17:21:35.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147441/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147441/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-10","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people have been employed in administering tax credits in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sammy Wilson","East Antrim","Sammy Wilson","214044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147442","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-17","<p>Treasury Ministers and officials receive regular correspondence on a wide range of issues. We cannot disclose details of specific representations.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government appreciates the real difficulties and the serious implications the Connaught issue has had for investors and is following the situation closely.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-11-17T16:48:59.613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147442/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147442/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-10","Connaught Income Series 1 Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent representations his Department has received on the Connaught Income Series 1 Fund.","false","Biography information for Guto Bebb","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","214075"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147443","HM Treasury","false","2014-11-19","<p>The information is not held.</p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel","214067","2014-11-19T13:59:07.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147443/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147443/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/147443/answer",,,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2014-11-10","Social Security Benefits: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many benefit claims have been made by adults in the UK in respect of children resident in another country since 2010.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","214066"
